Chevy's seems to be our go-to "large group" place for lunch at work.
They can easily accommodate a large group on little to short notice and the food is decent quality.
Yes, it's a chain, and yes there is definitely better Mexican Food in the Valley, but it works for what it is; fast, tasty, reasonably priced, and decent service.
I had a burrito and it was HUGE!
I couldn't eat it all, and then I went off and left it sitting on the table.
Silly me.
Oh well.
Parking is usually easy to find and we were in and out in less than an hour.
I think I've found another "Best Lunchtime Eats" candidate here.

Good chips, decent service.
Overall the food wasn't very good except for a little pile of sweet corn tamale mash that should be highlighted rather than underplayed....as it was the best thing there!
Well, the steak fajita nachos were ok too.
They didn't mind kids being a little rowdy and the tortilla machine was cute.
I'll come back with kids.
But only if I can have a margarita next time.

When I think of getting Mexican food, Chevy's is the first place that comes to mind.
It's close to the Biltmore, which gives it an ideal location.
The food is fresh, chips are fantastic!
And the guacamole is made right before your eyes.
I found that the staff here are very friendly and welcoming, though it's surprising that I've never seen the place even half full!
However, the food is great and portions are plentiful.
Chevy's is the place to go for great Mexican food at a great price.

